Authorized Representative, You agree to pay the Copyright Holder an
unauthorized-use fee.

15A.2. The unauthorized-use fee shall be the greater of: (a) the fees that would
have been payable under the Copyright Holder's then-current commercial,
organizational, network-use, SaaS, AI/ML, or equivalent license terms for the
entire period of unauthorized use; (b) the fair market value of the unauthorized
license, use, deployment, distribution, or exploitation; or (c) any minimum
amount stated in a separate written pricing schedule, commercial terms page,
invoice, order form, or commercial license policy published or provided by the
Copyright Holder.

15A.3. The parties acknowledge that damages from unauthorized use of source code,
commercial deployment, organizational adoption, AI/ML ingestion, network use,
distribution of modified versions, loss of licensing opportunities, loss of
market exclusivity, loss of control over proprietary software, security review,
investigation, enforcement, takedown, and reputational harm may be difficult to
calculate precisely. The unauthorized-use fee is intended as a reasonable
pre-estimate of harm and reasonable compensation, not as an unenforceable
penalty.

15A.4. To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, the unauthorized-use fee
is without prejudice to the Copyright Holder's right to seek injunctive relief,
specific performance, takedown, deletion, destruction of unauthorized copies,
copyright damages, infringer profits, statutory damages where available,
attorneys' fees, investigation costs, audit costs, collection costs, court costs,
arbitration costs, expert fees, and any other remedy available under contract,
copyright, patent, trademark, trade-secret, unfair-competition, civil, criminal,
or other applicable law.

15A.5. For jurisdictions that treat this section as a liquidated-damages clause,
the amount recoverable shall be limited to the maximum amount enforceable under
applicable law. If a court or competent authority finds the amount excessive,
invalid, or unenforceable, the amount shall be reduced and reformed to the
maximum enforceable amount that most closely preserves the Copyright Holder's
economic and protective intent.

15A.6. For Brazil, this section is intended, to the extent applicable, as a
"cláusula penal compensatória" and as a minimum indemnification amount for
unauthorized use, with express reservation of supplemental indemnification for
proven damages exceeding the penalty, to the maximum extent permitted by
applicable law.

15A.7. Payment of an unauthorized-use fee does not create a license, cure the
breach, reinstate terminated rights, or authorize continued use of the Software
